indicators = {
    "SI.POV.DDAY": "Poverty Headcount Ratio",
    "SI.POV.GAPS": "Poverty Gap Ratio",
    "SI.POV.GINI": "Gini Coefficient",
    "SI.DST.10TH.10": "Top 10% Income Share",
    "SI.DST.04TH.20": "Bottom 40% Income Share",
    "SI.DST.05TH.20": "Middle Class Income Share",
}

data = data[data["Indicator Code"].isin(indicators.keys())].iloc[:, :-1]
data.drop(["Country Code", "Indicator Code"], axis=1, inplace=True)
In [5]:
# Pivot the data to have 'Country Name', 'Indicator Name', and 'Year' as columns
data = data.melt(id_vars=['Country Name', 'Indicator Name'], var_name='Year', value_name='Value')

# Filter the data for the required years (you can adjust the range as needed)
data = data[(data['Year'] >= '2000') & (data['Year'] <= '2018')]

# Convert the 'Year' column to datetime
data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y')
In [6]:
def visualize_indicator(data, indicator_name, title):
    # Filter the data for the specified indicator
    indicator_data = data[data['Indicator Name'] == indicator_name]

    # Pivot the data to have 'Country Name' and 'Year' as indices
    indicator_data = indicator_data.pivot_table(index=['Country Name', 'Year'], columns='Indicator Name', values='Value').reset_index()

    # Create a line chart
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=indicator_data, x='Year', y=indicator_name, hue='Country Name', ci=None)

    # Set the title and labels
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel(indicator_name)

    # Show the legend
    plt.legend(title='Country')

    # Display the chart
    plt.show()

Let's select group of countries that share geographical, economical diversity.

# Five countries representing different regions and income levels
selected_countries = ['United States', 'China', 'India', 'Brazil', 'South Africa']

# Filter the data to include only the selected countries
filtered_data = data[data['Country Name'].isin(selected_countries)]
In [8]:
# Visualize the Poverty Headcount Ratio
visualize_indicator(filtered_data, "Poverty headcount ratio at $1.90 a day (2011 PPP) (% of population)", "Poverty Headcount Ratio by Country (2000-2018)")
# Visualize the Poverty Gap Ratio
visualize_indicator(filtered_data, "Poverty gap at $1.90 a day (2011 PPP) (%)", "Poverty Gap Ratio by Country (2000-2018)")
# Visualize the Gini Coefficient
visualize_indicator(filtered_data, "GINI index (World Bank estimate)", "Gini Coefficient by Country (2000-2018)")
# Visualize the Income Distribution
visualize_indicator(filtered_data, "Income share held by highest 10%", "Top 10% Income Share by Country (2000-2018)")
